                                     Our Verdict 

                         Credit One Bank is an online-only financial institution known for its portfolio of  credit cards , but the bank also offers high-yield savings and certificate of deposit (CD) accounts—both of which come with competitive rates and terms. You’ll need a high $100,000 minimum balance to open either type of account, so Credit One Bank is best for people who have a lot of money saved and want to earn high yield without shouldering the risk that investing entails. 
 This Credit One Bank review focuses on its savings and CD accounts. All account details and annual percentage yields (APYs) are current as of April 25, 2024. 





