 Credit One offers two banking products for customers with different needs: a jumbo high-yield savings account and jumbo CDs. 
 Credit One High Yield Savings Account 
 Credit One offers just one savings account option, but it has an appealing set of terms. This jumbo  high-yield savings account  earns 5.05% APY automatically but can earn a 0.05% increase if you also have a CD with the bank and qualify for the loyalty rate program. The account charges no monthly maintenance fee. 
 To open a savings account, you’ll need a minimum deposit of $100,000. If you dip below this minimum amount after your account is opened, Credit One will notify you to increase your balance. This is a steep requirement, so this account won’t be a good fit for everyone even though it’s free and earns a competitive rate. There are many  free savings accounts  with no minimum balance requirement and similar or better rates. 
 CDs 
 Credit One also offers two different CD accounts: the Credit One Bump-Up Jumbo Certificate of Deposit and Credit One High-Yield Jumbo Certificates of Deposit. Like high-yield savings accounts, both require a minimum balance of $100,000 to open and come with top-notch APYs. All CDs come with a 10-day rate guarantee too, meaning if rates go up in the first 10 days of your term, Credit One will automatically increase your rate to the higher one. 
 With the Bump-Up Jumbo CD, you also have the opportunity to opt into a one-time rate bump if APYs go up during your term. Customers can choose between two different term lengths: 24 months at 4.20% APY or 36 months at 4.05% APY. 
 The High-Yield Jumbo CD offers a wider range of term options and equally competitive rates. If you renew either CD account, you’ll qualify for the loyalty rate program, increasing your rate by 0.05%. 
